"{\"uid\": \"thefederalist.com-2024-08-08-olympics-boxing-fiasco-is-more-proof-men-dont-belong-in-womens-sports\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"It's baffling that we have gotten this far.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 43, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the first of this month, Italian female boxer Angela Carini matched up against Algeria's Imane Khelif, but the fight did not last long.\", \"from\": 45, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 80, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.975996641677358, \"rank\": 0.018557122913816636, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 94, \"end\": 107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 127, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999973305734033, \"rank\": 1.8530365763825148e-06, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 137, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After enduringtwo punches to the face, Carini left the Olympic women's boxing match 46 seconds in,sayingshe had \\\"never taken a punch like that.\\\"\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999154551876746, \"rank\": 8.455196072296777e-05, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She dejectedly collapsed in the ring and pronounced the fight \\\"unjust.\\\"\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif is one of two boxers in women's boxing who is in the middle of a controversy involving failedeligibility requirementsplaced by the International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 540, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4295190046807992e-27, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, the IBA president told Russian news that the boxers had XY chromosomes based on agenetic test.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9978198946209512, \"rank\": 0.0014159148394395282, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 608, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9892966073716835, \"rank\": 0.01071047610471379, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the IBA disqualified Khelif and the other boxer, the International Olympic Committee allowed them to compete, calling intoquestionthe IOC's safety standards for women's sports.\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9978198946209512, \"rank\": 0.0014159148394395282, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 739, \"end\": 770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.661641767057335e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For her part, Carini followed up bysayingin the aftermath that her decision stemmed from having \\\"the maturity to stop\\\" and wished her opponent well in future matches.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999154551876746, \"rank\": 8.455196072296777e-05, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In light of the firestorm of knee-jerk reactions, accusations, and name-calling that took place on social media once the story broke, it's worth taking a beat and asking ourselves: Why are we having this impassioned debate in the first place?\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Payton McNabb of North Carolinasuffered a severe injuryin September 2022 when, during a high school volleyball match, an opponent spiked the ball into her face, resulting in a concussion and neck injury that led to impaired vision, partial facial paralysis, headaches, anxiety, and depression - not to mention the hit knocked out some of her teeth.\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1275, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Payton\", \"score\": 0.999999828085962, \"rank\": 1.719092771188058e-07, \"text\": \"Payton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Payton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Payton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of the injury, she could not compete in her final volleyball season.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Massachusetts, a girls' high school basketball teamforfeited a gameat halftime after several players suffered injuries at the hand of another player, with the coach saying his roster was depleted just days before a playoff game.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"score\": 0.6431573565653883, \"rank\": 0.5547055832890813, \"text\": \"Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few months before in the same state, a girls' field hockey playersuffered a painful injurywhen she was struck in the face by a ball.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports injuries are an unfortunate reality, especially in high-contact sports such as the ones mentioned above.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a common thread in all of these instances is that these girls suffered injuries caused by reportedly male athletes.\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's one thing to compete against someone on an equal playing field; it's completelydemoralizingto square up against someone with natural physical advantages that not only significantly decrease your chances of victory but also increase the risk of injury.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While international sports leagues like theInternational Rugby LeagueandWorld Aquaticshave recognized the harm in allowing men to compete against women, the Biden-Harris administration is actively working to continue this dangerous trajectory for women's sports.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2722, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Biden-Harris administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The administration worked to tamper with federal law bychangingthe definition of \\\"sex\\\" in Title IX to include \\\"gender identity\\\" - a change that went into effect just asKatie LedeckyandSimone Bilesbecame two of the most decorated female athletes in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2919, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.145863952843172e-24, \"text\": \"Title IX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this rule change is allowed to stand, girls who look up to athletes like Ledecky and Biles could be relegated to bystanders in their own sports.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A law change like this would elevate the situations highlighted in North Carolina and Massachusetts to a national scale.\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3309, \"end\": 3323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\", \"score\": 0.9616965604682933, \"rank\": 0.03925373778843906, \"text\": \"North Carolina\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina_Tar_Heels\"}, {\"begin\": 3328, \"end\": 3341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"score\": 0.6431573565653883, \"rank\": 0.5547055832890813, \"text\": \"Massachusetts\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And up-and-coming female athletes would not be the only ones affected; all girls would see their private spaces - from locker rooms to hotel rooms on overnight trips - be open to male students.\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alliance Defending Freedom, where I serve as legal counsel, is part of a large group of organizations and states trying to stop the effort to effectively erase needed distinctions between the sexes.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In\\u00a0five\\u00a0different lawsuits, we have achievedfiveinjunctions, or pauses, on the rule change, which takes effect while the cases proceed.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are involved in defending state laws, likeIdaho'sandWest Virginia's, that protect women's athletics.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, as the emotional conversation around the Olympic boxing controversy showed, it's baffling that we have gone this far.\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Women deserve privacy, safety, and a fair chance to compete.\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4187, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletic associations and government officials need to open their eyes to this reality and stand in favor of women against an ideology that threatens their unique place in humanity.\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 The Federalist, A wholly independent division of FDRLST Media.\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4461, \"entities\": []}]}"